# Tech Stack — Canonical Reference

## Runtime & Language

| Item | Value | Constraint |
|---|---|---|
| **Node.js** | LTS | Align with NestJS-supported release |
| **TypeScript** | Strict mode | `strictNullChecks: true`, `noImplicitAny: true` — never use `any` |

## Infrastructure

| Layer | Technology | Note |
|---|---|---|
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | Accessed only via Prisma ORM |
| **ORM** | `prisma` + `@prisma/client` | Use Cases must NOT import Prisma directly |
| **Cache** | Redis | Cache-Aside Pattern; used in Auth Guard for `SessionContext` — spec: `docs/specs/common/01-api-context/README.md` |

## Framework — NestJS

| Component | Usage |
|---|---|
| Controllers | HTTP layer only — thin pass-through to Use Cases |
| Guards | Auth + RBAC (`RolesGuard`); JWT parsing happens here, not in Use Cases |
| Interceptors / Pipes | Global validation pipe with `whitelist: true`, `forbidNonWhitelisted: true` |
| Modules / DI | Feature-scoped modules; inject Repository interfaces, not implementations |
| `@nestjs/config` | All env vars must go through `ConfigService` — never hardcode secrets |

## Libraries

| Library | Purpose | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| `nestjs-cls` | `RequestContext` (`x-request-id`, IP, UA) + `SessionContext` (adminId, role, permissions) | Read from `cls.get()` in Use Cases; never pass via `execute()` params |
| `class-validator` | DTO field validation | Required on all request DTOs |
| `class-transformer` | DTO transforms | Pair `@Transform` with BrandedType boundaries |

## Type System

| Category | Type | Source |
|---|---|---|
| Unique identifiers (IDs) | `BrandedType<T, K>` | Import from `@common/types/brand.type.ts` only |
| Sensitive values (tokens, passwords, keys) | `StrictDataType<T, K>` | Extends `BrandedType`; cannot assign plain `string` — see `101-sensitive-data.mdc` |
| Plain `string` | **Forbidden** for IDs / sensitive fields | Use branded types at every boundary |

## Architecture Patterns

| Pattern | Rule |
|---|---|
| **Use Case** | One class, one `execute()`. No God Services. No CQRS. |
| **Repository** | Use Cases depend on interfaces only (`I*Repository`) |
| **Mapper** | Prisma model ↔ Domain Entity ↔ Response DTO via `*Mapper` class |
| **API Contract** | Return `CommonResponse<TResponseDto, TError>` — errors as values, no throws — see `100-response-control.mdc` |

Full structure & naming: `100-project-strcuture.mdc`.

## Testing

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| **Runner** | Vitest (`vi`, `describe`, `it`, `expect`) |
| **Pattern** | AAA + Table-Driven `TestCase[]` |
| **Location** | `test/` mirrors `src/` — no collocated test files |
| **Coverage** | 80% minimum per function; 100% for utilities |

Full conventions: `000-unit-test.mdc`.

## Forbidden

| What | Why |
|---|---|
| `$queryRaw` / `$executeRaw` with string interpolation | SQL injection risk |
| Prisma imports in Use Cases or Domain Entities | Violates Repository abstraction |
| `throw new HttpException` in Use Cases | Errors must be returned as values |
| Plain `string` for branded/sensitive fields | Type safety contract |
| Hardcoded secrets or magic error strings | Use `ConfigService` and `*.error.const.ts` |
